🦠 Microbiome Research Notes

This repository contains the research I independently compiled while developing a concept for a 
Personalised Microbiome Engineering and Gut-Brain Axis Optimisation Platform.


The Idea

Most probiotics, diets, and supplements fail because they treat everyone the same. 
But your gut microbiome is as unique as a fingerprint — shaped by your genetics, where you grew up, what you eat, and even how you were born.
Two people with identical genetics can have completely different health outcomes because of their microbiomes.

The platform I'm developing aims to fix that.
By combining genomic sequencing, microbiome analysis, and AI-driven recommendations,
it would generate truly personalised gut-brain optimisation plans — including custom probiotic/prebiotic formulations,
dietary guidance, and lifestyle interventions — and adapt them over time through continuous monitoring.

The gut-brain axis is the communication highway between your gut and your brain. 
It regulates mood, immunity, cognition, and digestion. 
Optimising it at an individual level is one of the most underexplored opportunities in precision medicine.


What's in this repo


